  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small pieces</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1631104984738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1631104984738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1631104984738-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1631104984738-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1631104984738-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a<strong> </strong>generous<strong> </strong>drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potato </strong>with the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and cook, covered, for an initial 6-7 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1631104988100-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1631104988100-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1631104988100-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1631104988100-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1631104988100-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice finely</p><p>Peel and dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1631104992104-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1631104992104-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1631104992104-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1631104992104-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1631104992104-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 6-7 min, add your <strong>smoked paprika</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced pepper </strong>and<strong> onion</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>diced chorizo </strong>and cook for 7-8 min further or until starting to crisp – this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>chorizo hash</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1631104996047-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1631104996047-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1631104996047-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1631104996047-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1631104996047-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>soured cream</strong> and <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Just add a little!) in a bowl and mix well – this is your <strong>garlic soured cream</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1631105001223-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1631105001223-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1631105001223-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1631105001223-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1631105001223-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> to a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to the bowl and gently mix together – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1631105005137-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1631105005137-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1631105005137-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1631105005137-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1631105005137-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>eggs</strong> into the pan and cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your eggs a little shake before you crack for perfectly centred yolks!</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1631105009153-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1631105009153-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1631105009153-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1631105009153-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1631105009153-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fried egg</strong> over the top of the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>chorizo hash </strong>with the<strong> dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Dollop over some <strong>garlic soured cream</strong></p><p>Garnish with <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
